===Etymology===
From earlier {{m|en|slughorn|sloggorne, slughorne|t=battle cry}}, borrowed from {{bor|en|gd|sluagh-ghairm|t=battle cry}}, from {{der|en|sga|slúag}}, {{m|sga|slóg|t=army}}, from {{der|en|cel-pro|*slougos|t=troop, army}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*slowgʰo-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*slowgo-|t=entourage}} + {{der|en|sga|gairm|t=a call, cry}}, from {{der|en|cel-pro|*garman-}}, {{m|cel-pro|*garrman-|t=a call, shout}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*ǵh₂r-smn-}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*ǵh₂r-|t=to shout, call}}. Compare {{cog|la|garriō|t=I chatter}}, {{cog|ang|caru|t=sorrow, care}}, {{cog|sa|श्लोक|t=verse,call}}.

